Package es.weso.asio.ontology.test

Class TestCase

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.weso.asio.ontology.test.TestCase
  • public class TestCase
extends java.lang.Object
    This models a test case, which is composed of a name, the ontology that is being tested, the data to test, the schema against the tests will be thrown, the input shape map, which specifies the nodes that will be tested. And the output expected shape map.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TestCase

        public TestCase​(java.lang.String name,
                java.lang.String ontologyFilePath,
                java.lang.String dataFilePath,
                java.lang.String testSchemaFilePath,
                java.lang.String testShapeMapFilePath,
                java.lang.String expectedShapeMapFilePath)
        The default constructor is a basic all-args constructor. All the arguments that it takes are paths to the different files, except the name that is the literal string that will be assigned as test name.
        Parameters:
        name - of the test case.
        ontologyFilePath - is the file path to the ontology file used for testing.
        dataFilePath - is the file path to the data file used to mock ontology instances.
        testSchemaFilePath - is the file path to the schema used to validate the ontology.
        testShapeMapFilePath - is the file path to the shape map that relates each test data node with its corresponding schema.
        expectedShapeMapFilePath - is the file path to the expected result shape map.
